meanings.definition: Print (something) on top of an existing print.
meanings.sent1: She surprinted her signature on the document.
meanings.sent2: The company logo was surprinted onto the packaging.
meanings.sent3: The cat accidentally surprinted its paw on the wet paint.
meanings.sent4: His laughter surprinted the room, filling it with joy.
meanings.sent5: The artist's brush surprinted vibrant colors onto the canvas.

meanings.definition: A printed image or text that is superimposed on another print.
meanings.sent1: The magazine cover featured a surprinted headline.
meanings.sent2: The poster had a surprinted map in the background.
meanings.sent3: The surprinted message on the flyer caught everyone's attention.
meanings.sent4: Her smile was like a surprinted image of happiness.
meanings.sent5: The surprinted design on the shirt was eye-catching.
